        <abstract>
            <p>Birth of his sixth son [C. W. Darwin]. It is dreadful "to think of all the sendings to school and the professions afterwards".</p>
            <p>CD is not well but has not the courage for water-cure again; trying mineral acids.</p> 
<p>Working hard on the book [<hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi>]; is overwhelmed with riches in facts and interested in way facts fall into groups.</p> 
            <p>To his surprise [Helix pomatia] has withstood 14 days in salt water.</p>
            <p>Pigeons’ skins come in from all parts of the world.</p>
        </abstract>
